The test file from US-100 has 16 tests covering normalization, determinism, and seed variation. US-101 requires condition gating to also be tested. I need to implement `evaluateCondition` + `filterAvailableBranches` in `dialogueBranch.ts` and add tests.

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The spec §33.4 defines conditions as a gating mechanism on `DialogueBranch.conditions[]` — a branch is only available if ALL its conditions are satisfied
- The workflow (docs→tests→code) means condition gating must live in the same pure-function module (`dialogueBranch.ts`) so it stays testable without ECS/R3F
- `DialogueContext` acts as a plain value object injected at test time — it decouples the pure evaluation from the game store, enabling deterministic unit tests
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
